de.tif.jacob.core.definition
Interface IKey

All Superinterfaces:
INamedObjectDefinition
public interface IKey
extends INamedObjectDefinition

This interface represents an abstraction of data source table keys. Keys could be either of the following:

  • a primary key
  • a foreign key
  • an unique or non-unique index

    convertStringToKeyValue

    IDataKeyValue convertStringToKeyValue(java.lang.String keyvalueStr)
                                      throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException

    convertKeyValueToString

    java.lang.String convertKeyValueToString(IDataKeyValue keyvalue)
                                         throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
    Converts a given key value to a string representation.

    This string representation can be converted back by means of convertStringToKeyValue(String).

    Note: Do not use IDataKeyValue.toString(), if the resulting string should be re-converted to a key value object!

    Parameters:
    keyvalue - the key value object
    Returns:
    the key value string representation
    Throws:
    java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if key and key value are not compatible
    Since:
    2.10
